Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
earlyGlobalRoute(25.10)                                earlyGlobalRoute(25.10)

Name
       earlyGlobalRoute  -  Early  Global  Route (earlyGlobalRoute) is a quick
       global routing for estimating routing-related  congestion and parasitic
       (resistance and capacitance) values

Syntax
       earlyGlobalRoute

       [-help]

       Early Global Route (earlyGlobalRoute) is a quick global routing for es-
       timating routing-related  congestion and parasitic (resistance and  ca-
       pacitance) values. The Early Global Route results are also used for pin
       assignment  when  you  commit partitions in hierarchical designs. Early
       Global Route does not guarantee DRC-clean routing results. Do not  per-
       form  signal  integrity analysis on a design that has been routed using
       Early Global Route, because these routes are only used to estimate par-
       asitic values for timing analysis. Route  designs  with  the  NanoRoute
       router if you want to perform signal integrity analysis.

       Wire  overlap can occur if a gcell is only partially covered by a rout-
       ing blockage or pre-routed wires. Overlapping of non-default rule wires
       can also occur during track assignment; however,  this  information  is
       modeled  when  the  router estimates congestion. You can use the early-
       GlobalRoute command after running placement. If the design  uses  addi-
       tional  placement  features,  such  as  clock  tree  synthesis and scan
       groups, use the command after running these placement features. If  you
       have run IPO commands on your design, you must run the earlyGlobalRoute
       command to update interconnections for the design.

       Notes:

              * You  can  set the global parameters for the Early Global Route
                program by using the setRouteMode command. Parameters that you
                specify with setRouteMode are then used automatically whenever
                you run Early Global Route, either explicitly through the ear-
                lyGlobalRoute command or internally during in-place  optimiza-
                tion, partitioning, or placement.

              * The assignPtnPin command reports the number of guide pins from
                route  guides  and  fixed pins. Since earlyGlobalRoute chooses
                guide points provided by assignPtnPin to lay wires  on  parti-
                tion boundary, the earlyGlobalRoute report clearly differenti-
                ates  between  fixed  pins  and  the pins which are in the pin
                guide.

              * The Early Global Router supports nested partitions. The parti-
                tions specified with the setRouteMode  -earlyGlobalRouteParti-
                tionHonorFence  and  the  setRouteMode -earlyGlobalRouteParti-
                tionHonorPin parameters are routed in the  style  that  honors
                fence  and  pin  constraints.  All  other partitions are still
                routed flat.

              * The Early Global Router supports get_metric APIs  and  enables
                you  to query existing routing metrics at command line. To en-
                able this capability, routeDesign just calls the 'get_metrics'
                API after generating the routing metrics.

              * If bus guides have been created in the GUI,  the  earlyGlobal-
                Route command honors the bus guides automatically.

              * The  earlyGlobalRoute  command honors multiple-CPU setting for
                track assignment inside earlyGlobalRoute by default.

              * The Early Global Router supports blackboxes by default. It in-
                ternally calls the assignPtnPin command and places and  routes
                all unplaced blackbox pins.

              * The  Early  Global  Router supports uses two-row-height gcells
                with congestion modelling improvement for the technology nodes
                whose row-height is smaller than 7 track. It  uses  2x2  gcell
                size  as  default  for  small default gcell size (<=7). By de-
                fault, it checks for the number of tracks rather than checking
                the technology of the design to grow gcell size.

                Note: This enhancement is designed  only  for  N7  designs  as
                these  designs  have  less  than 7 tracks. If an N7 design has
                more than 7 tracks then these setting will not be  applied  in
                order to ensure a better congestion accuracy.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each earlyGlobalRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

               man earlyGlobalRoute.

Example
              * The following command honors partition fences with single  en-
                try  and does not allow crossing other partitions, when early-
                GlobalRoute is run:

                setRouteMode -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence {.}

                earlyGlobalRoute

              * The following command does quick global routing for estimating
                routing-related  congestion and parasitic values.

                earlyGlobalRoute

